cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with capacity scaling of a large hybrid network with wireless ad hoc nodes and base stations equipped with multiple antennas. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper analyzes achievable throughput scaling laws based on information-theoretic operating regimes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing the performance of different routing protocols in the network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing the throughput scaling of a network with multiple antennas at each base station. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing the performance of different routing protocols in a distributed network.
